:INFO
Open Source SaaS Business
Running a business on an open source product combines community-driven growth with commercial monetization. The open core model offers a self-hosted free tier and a managed cloud tier with additional features and support.

:COUNTER.half
1,000 GitHub Stars
Early signal of sustainable community interest
|
:COUNTER.half
10x Users
Typical ratio of self-hosted to cloud tier users

:PATH
Open Source Phase
Design the core product as fully open source under a permissive or source available license. Make self-hosting straightforward with a single-command Docker setup.

:PATH
Community Phase
Invest in documentation, issue response time, and contributor experience. Community health drives organic discovery more than any paid channel.

:PATH
Monetize Phase
Offer a managed cloud tier with convenience and compliance features. Add enterprise support contracts and SSO as gated paid features.

:CHECKLIST
Open Source SaaS Checklist
[ ] Choose license: MIT, Apache, AGPL, or SSPL
[ ] Write clear README with quickstart guide
[ ] Set up Docker Compose for self-hosting
[ ] Create public roadmap and issue labels
[ ] Define the open core boundary: what is free, what is paid
[ ] Launch on Hacker News Show HN and GitHub Trending
[ ] Set up cloud tier infrastructure
[ ] Create pricing page with clear tier comparison
[ ] Respond to every GitHub issue within 48 hours

:NOTE
The open source project is a marketing channel as much as a product. Treat the developer experience of your self-hosted version as seriously as your cloud product. Bad self-hosting documentation kills community trust.

